RACE.RACE_TEXT: RUIDOSO DOWNS RACE 2 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 59. Maiden Claiming Purse 11600. FOR MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000. New Mexico Bred Claiming Price $7,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: NOGAL CANYON pressed the pace along the inside, angled out on the turn, challenged three across, dueled through the stretch in tight quarters, exchanged bumps and prevailed. TEE ROY vied throughout, was in tight and exchanged bumps in the stretch and was outfinished in a good effort. HOLLYWOOD TIZ was off a step slowly, lagged early while racing six wide along the backstretch, advanced around the turn and finished well to earn show. W F JAZZ CAT bumped at the start, vied to the turn and gave way. TOO HOT FOR YOU raced close to the pace, went five wide along the backstretch, rallied into the turn, bid and came up empty. GEEBEESBIGBOY came in at the start, pressed the pace, dropped inside on the turn and stopped. EL OCHO dropped inside, raced mid pack, was not urged in the stretch and showed little. HOLLYWOOD DAX broke slowly, bumped and was pinched back at the start, was restrained early, swung wide leaving the turn and not urged late. The rider of TEE ROY lodged an objection against the rider of NOGAL CANYON for alleged interference in the stretch. No change was made. PER HIWU RULING, TEE ROY WAS DISQUALIFIED FROM 2nd TO UNPLACED DUE TO BEING INELIGIBLE TO COMPETE PER RULE 4222.
